===Etymology 1===
{{zh-forms|s=献|alt=𤡎}}
Same word as {{och-l|憲}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), its basic meaning being seemingly "elevate > to be elavated".

Inside the Sinitic branch of the Sino-Tibetan language family, it's related to {{och-l|甗|a cooking vessel consisting of a steamer 'elevated' on a three-legged boiler}}. Furthermore, it's possibly cognate to {{cog|bo|སྔར་མ||sharp-witted, quick-witted, intelligent}} (ibid., {{zh-ref|Gong, 2000}}).

